{"about_the_game":"We always understood why and how one experiences emotions, but we could never <i><strong>see</strong></i> why.<br><br>This changed, however, once a governmental medical institution made a discovery. A way to manifest human thoughts and emotions into a <strong><i>visible entity</i></strong>.<br>To monitor these entities, a Japanese prefecture has been turned into a labyrinth-like net of hospitals. All of this is for the sake of acquiring complete emotional stability through the removal of illegal emotional states.<br><br>In this environment, a young distressed student named Lia experiences her inner problems through many changes in her own <i><strong>manifestation of emotions</strong></i>. Can you help Lia cope with her emotions and her inner voice through your choices<br>...or will you give in to your negative thoughts?<br><br><strong>Features:</strong><br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>A Hand-drawn game</strong> - a comic style visual novel </li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Branching narrative</strong> - your choices do make a difference; explore different emotional states Lia can find herself in through other available choices </li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Multiple endings</strong> - replay the game, and you may get a different ending; choices change the state of your &quot;emotion scanner&quot; you'll see pop up in the corner of your screen from time to time, maybe you can let it guide you</li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Minigame</strong> - a simple multiple-choice game that will help you get desired emotions; help Lia navigate through her feelings and focus on the wanted outcome </li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Original story and Art</strong> - a stylized approach to a dystopian world </li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Original soundtrack</strong> - musical ambiance for the exploration of an emotion-monitored world </li></ul>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"name":"The tablet's glow was differ